on(socket.getOutputStream(), newSessionResponse());\n            } else if (\"DELETE\".equals(method) && path.startsWith(\"/session/\")) {\n                writeJson(socket.getOutputStream(), \"{\\\"value\\\":null}\");\n            } else {\n                writeJson(socket.getOutputStream(), \"{\\\"value\\\":null}\");\n            }\n        }\n\n        private int readContentLength(BufferedReader reader) throws IOException {\n            int contentLength = 0;\n            String line;\n            while ((line = reader.readLine()) != null && !line.isEmpty()) {\n                String lowerCaseLine = line.toLowerCase(Locale.ROOT);\n                if (lowerCaseLine.startsWith(\"content-length:\")) {\n                    contentLength = Integer.parseInt(line.substring(line.indexOf(':') + 1).trim());\n                }\n            }\n            return contentLength;\n        }\n\n        private String newSessionResponse() {\n            return \"\"\"\n                    {\n                      \"value\": {\n                        \"sessionId\": \"test-session\",\n                        \"capabilities\": {\n                          \"browserName\": \"firefox\",\n                          \"browserVersion\": \"1.0\",\n                          \"platformName\": \"linux\",\n                          \"acceptInsecureCerts\": false,\n                          \"pageLoadStrategy\": \"normal\",\n                          \"setWindowRect\": true,\n                          \"timeouts\": {\n                            \"implicit\": 0,\n                            \"pageLoad\": 300000,\n                            \"script\": 30000\n                          },\n                          \"unhandledPromptBehavior\": \"dismiss and notify\"\n                        }\n                      }\n                    }\n                    \"\"\";\n        }\n\n        private void writeJson(OutputStream outputStream, String json) throws IOException {\n            byte[] body = json.getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8);\n            String headers = \"\"\"\n                    HTTP/1.1 200 OK\r\n\\\n                    Content-Type: application/json; charset=utf-8\r\n\\\n                    Content-Length: %d\r\n\\\n                    Connection: close\r\n\\\n                    \r\n\\\n                    \"\"\".formatted(body.length);\n            outputStream.write(headers.getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8));\n            outputStream.write(body);\n            outputStream.flush();\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void close() throws IOException, InterruptedException {\n            serverSocket.close();\n            executor.shutdownNow();\n            assertThat(executor.awaitTermination(TIMEOUT.toMillis(), TimeUnit.MILLISECONDS)).isTrue();\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}
[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating server implementation options**\n\nI'm considering using ServerSocket instead of the jdk.httpserver module to keep things minimal. Implementing an HTTP server with ServerSocket could be easier with multithreading while ensuring predictability. It seems Native image might need --add-modules for jdk.httpserver, which I'd like to avoid. If I go with TcpHttpServer, I should be cautious about connection handling, especially for DELETE requests. I could also think about adding a timeout for the accept loop for robustness. It might just make more sense to use ServerSocket from java.base for a smoother experience.\n\n**Designing a simple Selenium server**\n\nI'm working on creating a `FakeSeleniumServer` that implements `AutoCloseable`. It uses a `ServerSocket` and a single-threaded executor for handling requests. I'm considering how to manage connections, making sure it can handle multiple at once, perhaps sequentially. The `acceptLoop` accepts incoming sockets and processes them. I'll be using `BufferedReader` to read headers efficiently while ensuring I handle the request body correctly without blocking. Finally, the response will be formatted properly with the appropriate headers for JSON, using UTF-8 encoding for the body.\n\n**Implementing session handling**\n\nI'm trying to figure out how to use an `OutputStream` for handling requests. In the `handle` method, I'll extract the HTTP method and path from the incoming request. If the request is a POST to `/session`, I need to set up the body string, count down, and respond with JSON for a new session. If it's a DELETE request for `/session/test-session`, the response should be `{\"value\": null}`. I’m also thinking about whether I should include a GET request for `/status` before creating a new session.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_00b0b265a43ee47b0169fd5cd1469081a0b53d9f3958b4ac86\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp_Vze9XOzAG7dgLBq-qCMr0Xrge9YfvtHloaMNdV6-MqRU6rxmRmtC-KfCVUbNHqUNHUnzlSeNILWo0Y0KaOlsRD0wnqriwNPLgPsWyIou7JxsIEMrXEMgrxe3aiKD5tyATzBoUqEL5IqspqalLjNN50pdJm55heTSbL773E5Y1ovnIBzDbfmzfg8bW0ImE7Y1h75RKcyhwbSATTCzaxjbgEKxTDj-xaJvaa3FQOm-jpW-CkbVMeE4Oyc8ubyd5YM-NL9CYJWqZ84OO9Pl5h7FI3TGca_MkiwydN2BAXPoh_RSv3fOvpakOCjAWD3eOwyZpbW-m0qTbBx3qdgjBagrLV0w_CGkd67vnHoiEh_pJ2GrwkDckDEc1Aw98yvYljr2MQ09nWT_CSZ0gjLxrZ3fLrBMYsvnNYCIwk1j8fhhcmCqJDyC-7ABZNxkcYrO8bmErqZY94NWLN2aHWo_fDbvoM-XdwyPzrwLCRqQs38FCD0frV4v_wyEMFmTzDkfGWxccOwYTW5Th7j8Ij6FjKE8IycYajJ3gAcP-rfZeR5v27CSapbajzFGhInZ44VwQXfhpWVdLDd6l8r1d8Y63P8zAr1-ukwGnpD7kYLJIcEWdbdfurBhYBjVAQxs7E009iGqMyw0qu2TpzOTkKWnBfrSLAECux-hjDGIxZMRZGjZbSa-1swVtNqvQlFGjy9CNC0WCaVvOWs-mi3Xjmu9Vxvm-aWyb5fojAgKyeiJup7Xo5tZMRDimcmECmicpj3l8r22VNse7dIBHlP-Si7MJcTB2mI7UNubMHQSSzgNEwCPFgGWWzGo37fAZJaSBh7z8ZWg-eZcNpfguhZC_-6LTTXQVP34Vioei2t5tfJKR4Mxq202V7rkUwJTMLrNgm50nY0TE8EgbIyd07lb7_VOMs0ClajCuyZ2K1giJgdWO76nzlMWI15piKHKO0C3LI3wqpYSf-7lEVr4G-1SGm0NPfgHjJdT3rdVBcc7oRJjY7KausoenCBSwyC7dY9bK1ytLWfHUHI477QGVpDVzhCk7vJLl9Dstv8QXIYrGw6zdpXq-9nx6uZonj0WbycbzRP6P__wtZXKsRN9cvaVLY3eNbj7O-_smONMl7ys39mIc85FstdElVN7R2fX9q91ZM0AwKjFNXuv-JPtyAzBeZro2JCjMBOU0LsekTTXR6Jw8iDJ9Q_fUkbN-XsGp-gAB-o7dgI9yaIYXUy7OxdctSFR_KdFU__ErI6r_80HhBwZR3fq8SJB_zfLIswOozK2zvejLU1T9v2HFhrOj78CpvLXvkpgnf3MU0csuOKFDbC-5OufBNW8b9CqyxwHrF4KjPg-b04FfAdMD_PFMDeYRvd-0PXnZDu8uGCUvWcun6UjdYF6CN22HrgAP8iX3oiSRXGg_ITryU_KiteSVkKtQBak75RO5zxga_6l_LCB5DJ-ojR9LA7XXefibm5tL43NhkH8R1qY6rNzeRZn7HloL7U-n-iohuyPc3NbuC7I_hGS62sQqrq0xsjrtvj1wXIoMXK6vU3Ixp0mnIUeucX0cAF1NHhlRHkf4HWtXIXrSwRCwWLuSn_O6XZLxJCyBKjFUgsuZ4ffqM23Y3swTNhAYxC5EX_9Dxcc0MGlYGNt6p8xKo58_dJSW9AP5GIQ--T4fV_uMPLphB3wbC9dGiKit2h2wPX2te6tuk6A1eD_tMWFj7M31dOhEggdvTZtSrWLYMdiVx6PK1kFc_gDpXjeffgXFnxUjb-dt6LbspgVStBTiwOtXysaXcJtrAwxeX8S6IMBNBGAHTX-4vYkcnbnQe4NNrSHHyL_PDGZN2-r5RknSug5rcUiHAzn4AVP8ch3DnqgXYhnj-oIopVBnsK_61fwl0AB0vJA6fXX99P0jAfRErU4CAE6bLSoc0PUYxh0m6VXQL6-FqObMdf9eUGe121vXUSarOAZmHJhwXDn